# How To Run The Project

## Step 1 — Clone Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/Riktam45/moodlens-sentiment-chrome-extension.git
```

---

## Step 2 — Open Project Folder

```bash
cd moodlens-sentiment-chrome-extension
```

---

# Backend Setup

## Step 3 — Move to Backend Folder

```bash
cd backend-api
```

---

## Step 4 — Install Required Packages

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

---

## Step 5 — Run FastAPI Server

```bash
uvicorn main:app --reload
```

If successful, you will see:

```text
Uvicorn running on http://127.0.0.1:8000
```

Backend API will run on:

```text
http://127.0.0.1:8000
```

---

# Chrome Extension Setup

## Step 6 — Open Chrome Extensions Page

Open:

```text
chrome://extensions/
```

---

## Step 7 — Enable Developer Mode

Turn ON:

```text
Developer Mode
```

(top-right corner)

---

## Step 8 — Load Extension

Click:

```text
Load unpacked
```

Select:

```text
frontend-extension
```

inside the project folder.

---

# Using The Extension

## Step 9 — Open Social Media Post

Currently supported:
- YouTube
- Reddit

---

## Step 10 — Open MoodLens Extension

Paste:
- YouTube post URL
- Reddit post URL

Click:

```text
Analyze Post
```

The extension will:
1. Extract comments
2. Analyze sentiments
3. Display:
   - Positive %
   - Neutral %
   - Negative %
   - Total comments analyzed

---

# Manual Comment Analysis

You can also manually test a comment by:

1. Typing a comment
2. Clicking:

```text
Analyze Comment
```

The extension will display:
- Sentiment type
- Confidence score

---

# Troubleshooting

## Backend Not Starting

Make sure Python is installed:

```bash
python --version
```

---

## Extension Not Loading

Check:
- `manifest.json` exists
- Developer Mode is ON
- Correct folder selected

---

## API Connection Error

Make sure backend is running on:

```text
http://127.0.0.1:8000
```

before opening the extension.

